{"name": "rox-septentrio", "metadata": {"name": "rox-septentrio", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["paho-mqtt", "click", "coloredlogs", "orjson", "pydantic-settings", "pydantic", "pymap3d", "pynmea2", "pyserial"], "summary": "Driver for Septentrio GPS, posting messages to mqtt", "upload_time": 1735219186}, "documentation": ["# Septentrio GPS\n\n\n**What it does:**\n\n* Reads NMEA messages from the gps receiver (over serial or ip)\n* parses them and calculates ENU coordinates\n* publishes `latlon` and `enu` data as json to mqtt topics.\n\n**mqtt messages**\n\n```\ntopic: /gps/position\n{\"lat\":51.45655803,\"lon\":6.08187908,\"x\":-13.354,\"y\":-67.59,\"gps_qual\":4,\"time\":\"14:27:27.800000\",\"ts\":1726149158.437}\n\ntopic: /gps/direction\n{\"heading\":152.22,\"heading_stdev\":0.084,\"theta\":-1.0859,\"ts\":1726149158.441}\n```\n\n\n## 1. Configure receiver\n\nInstall and configure gps receiver as described in [installation manual](docs/README.md)\n\n\n## 2. Launch docker container\n\nget docker image (use tag for version)\n\n    registry.gitlab.com/roxautomation/components/septentrio-gps:latest\n\nlaunch container with\n\n    docker run \\\n    -e GPS_NODE_TYPE=ip \\\n    -e GPS_IP_HOST=<hostname> \\\n    registry.gitlab.com/roxautomation/components/septentrio-gps:latest\n\n\nSet these environment variables to override default settings:\n\n### MQTT\n- **MQTT_HOST**: MQTT server host (default: `\"localhost\"`).\n- **MQTT_PORT**: MQTT server port (default: `1883`).\n- **MQTT_POSITION_TOPIC**: MQTT topic for GPS positions (default: `\"/gps/position\"`).\n- **MQTT_DIRECTION_TOPIC**: MQTT topic for GPS directions (default: `\"/gps/direction\"`).\n\n### GPS\n- **GPS_NODE_TYPE**: \"serial\" or \"ip\" (default: `\"serial\"`).\n- **GPS_SERIAL_PORT**: Serial port for GPS (default: `\"/dev/gps_nmea\"`).\n- **GPS_SERIAL_BAUD**: Baud rate for GPS serial communication (default: `115200`).\n- **GPS_IP_HOST** : ip server address (default `localhost`)\n- **GPS_IP_PORT** : ip port (default `28000`)\n- **GPS_REF**: gps reference point, provide lat,lon, example: `GPS_REF=\"51.123,6.456\"`\n\n## Precision\n - **DIGITS_POSITION** : meter position accuracy, defaults to 3\n - **DIGITS_LATLON** : digits latitude and longitude, defaults to 8\n - **DIGITS_ANGLE** : angle accuracy, defaults to 4\n\n\n(note: configuration is defined in `config.py`)\n\n\n\n## Development\n\nThere should be mqtt broker available on the host system. If not, there is a docker image for that:\n\n    docker run -d --name mosquitto --restart unless-stopped -p 1883:1883 registry.gitlab.com/roxautomation/images/mosquitto:latest\n\n* Open in VSCode devcontainer. Virtual com port is located at `/tty/tty_nmea_rx`\n* Pre-recorded nmea stream can be sent to com port with `replay_data.py` in `integration/data` folder.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "rox_septentrio", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "rox_septentrio.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "rox_septentrio.PackageNotFoundError", "xref": {"fqname": "importlib.metadata.PackageNotFoundError", "project": null}}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.version", "xref": {"fqname": "importlib.metadata.version", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_serial", "documentation": ["GPS node. Reads NMEA data from serial, parses it and publishes to MQTT\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 ROX Automation - Jev Kuznetsov", "!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [{"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_serial.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_serial.LOG_FORMAT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_serial.LOGLEVEL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_serial.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip", "documentation": ["GPS node. Reads NMEA data from a socket, parses it and publishes to MQTT\nIncludes robust socket connection handling, complete type hints, and full stack traces on exceptions.\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 ROX Automation - Jev Kuznetsov", "!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [{"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip.connect_socket", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "gps_cfg", "type": {"name": "config.GpsConfig", "xref": {"fqname": "rox_septentrio.config.GpsConfig", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "socket.socket", "xref": {"fqname": "socket.socket", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip.LOG_FORMAT", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip.LOGLEVEL", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip.FEEDBACK_PERIOD", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_septentrio.gps_node_ip.log", "type": {"name": "logging.Logger", "xref": {"fqname": "logging.Logger", "proje